  <? else: ?>
    <p>No backups configured.</p>
  <? endif; ?>
  <blockquote class="inline_help">
    Unlike a sync, a backup is one-way and runs on a schedule: at the interval you choose,
    MEGAcmd takes a fresh snapshot of a local folder and uploads it to a new dated folder on
    MEGA, automatically deleting your oldest snapshot once you exceed the number you asked to
    keep. Files deleted locally are never removed from snapshots already uploaded. MEGA itself
    still labels this feature BETA.
  </blockquote>
</div>

<div class="megacmd-box">
  <h3>Backup history</h3>
  <? if (trim($backupHistory) !== "" && stripos($backupHistory, "No backup configured") === false): ?>
