    <small class="megacmd-hint">STATUS legend: COMPLETE, INCOMPLETE, ABORTED, MISCARRIED, SKIPPED.</small>
  <? else: ?>
    <p>No backup history yet.</p>
  <? endif; ?>
  <blockquote class="inline_help">
    A record of each individual scheduled backup run -- not the ongoing backup configuration
    itself (shown in "Current backups" above), but whether each past run finished. STATUS is one
    of: COMPLETE, INCOMPLETE (a transfer was cancelled or failed), ABORTED (manually cancelled
    mid-run), MISCARRIED (the service stopped mid-run), or SKIPPED (the service wasn't running
    when a run was due). This history belongs to the backup's own configuration -- if you remove
    a backup below, its history here disappears too, even though the transfers it already made
    still show up permanently in "Transfer history" above.
  </blockquote>
</div>

